The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, April 13: Credit rating agency Icra today surged 166.66 per cent on its debut trade on the Bombay Stock Exchange and settled at Rs 797.60 at the end of the trading session. On the National Stock Exchange, the scrip witnessed a similar trend as it closed the day at Rs 829, at a premium of 163.63 per cent over its issue price of Rs 330.

 New Delhi, April 13: Dissatisfied with French food company Danones explanation about its alleged violation of Press Note 1, the industry ministry will seek further clarification from the firm.

 Mumbai, April 13: Sebi today asked the Bombay Stock Exchange and National Stock Exchange to set up platforms to trade corporate bonds. The platforms are slated to become operational from July 1.

 Mumbai, April 13:Reliance Industries (RIL) has allotted 12 crore equity linked warrants on preferential basis to promoters. The issue, when fully converted into equity shares, will result in a fresh capital infusion of Rs 16,824 crore into the firm.

 Calcutta, April 13: Jai Balaji Group will amalgamate Jai Balaji Sponge and Shri Ramrupai Balaji Sponge. The move was approved at an EGM of the shareholders here.




